  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink258-kilavi">varaivu vēṇṭiviṭa maṟuttuḻit tamarkk uraippāḷāy varaiyātu vantoḻukum 
          talaimakaṟkut tōḻi yavaṉ malai kāṇṭalē paṟṟākat tāṅkaḷ uyir vāḻkiṉṟamai tōṉṟac colliyatu.
          </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">What the confidante—being one who, having requested marriage and been refused, spoke as one addressing her people—told the hero who kept coming without marrying, so as to make it apparent that they live, holding only the sight of his mountain as their support.   
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink258">
<l>kuṉṟak kuṟavaṉ kātaṉ maṭamaka</l>
<l>ḷaṇimayi laṉṉa vacainaṭaik koṭicciyaip</l>
<l>peruvarai nāṭaṉ varaiyu māyiṟ</l>
<l>koṭuttaṉe māyiṉō naṉṟē</l>
<l>yiṉṉu māṉātu naṉṉuta ṟuyarē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>If the man from the land of the great hills</l>
        <l>were to marry the girl like a creeper,</l>
        <l>with a swaying gait</l>
        <l>like that of the beautiful peacock,</l>
        
        <l rend="indent2">that beloved, naïve daughter</l>
        <l rend="indent2">of the hill dweller,</l>
        <l rend="space">only if we were to give her away,</l>
        <l>that would be good.</l>
        <l rend="space">[Otherwise], the suffering</l>
        <l>of her good forehead</l>
        <l>would not cease now.</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
